name: monosaccharide-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + monosaccharideout = ADP + phosphate + monosaccharidein [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. Family of bacterial enzymes importing ribose, xylose, arabinose, galactose and methylgalactoside.

orthologs.K02056: simple sugar transport system ATP-binding protein
orthologs.K10548: putative multiple sugar transport system ATP-binding protein
